As of the census of 2020, there were 850 households and 956 housing units in the borough. The racial makeup of the borough was 93.2% [[White (U.S. Census)|White]], 4.5% [[African American (U.S. Census)|African American]], and 2.3% from other races. The median income was $52,928.<ref>{{cite web |title=North Belle Vernon Borough |url=https://data.census.gov/profile/North_Belle_Vernon_borough,_Westmoreland_County,_Pennsylvania?g=060XX00US4212954776 |publisher=United States Census Bureau}}</ref>

